Communicative language learning takes place in a supportive environment, the choice of themes stems from the multitudes, current affairs and development needs. According to the subject, the vocabulary is fixed and the theoretical knowledge is appliedObjectives/eesmärkid:  This course is for foreign students, who will start their studies in Estonian language and spend the first year learning only Estonian. The course supports the development the level of Estonian language to the first language proficiency level (0-> A2). The aim of the course is to develop communication skills, to motivate independent language learning, to familiarize with Estonian society and its principles of operation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who passed the subject: - interacts in Estonian at his or her level of language; - actively uses the acquired vocabulary;  - if necessary, initiates a conversation, is able to ask questions in various communication situations and answer questions asked to him.
